#### Course Overview and Objectives

This course is designed to make students proficient and comfortable with Python. 
You'll learn to set up a robust development environment, master Git and GitHub, 
and delve into advanced Python programming concepts. The course will also cover 
Numpy, Matplotlib, and provide a thorough understanding of the Manim animation engine.

##Installing Python and Setting Upba Virtual Environment

1. Open your browser and navigate to [Python Downloads](https://www.python.org/downloads/).
2. Choose the version you want to install and download it.
3. Go to your download folder and run the Python installer.
4. To check the installation, open your terminal and type `python --version`, then press Enter. 
   This will confirm that Python is installed correctly and added to your PATH.
5. To install packages, open the terminal and type `pip install package_name`.

# Introduction to Integrated Development Environments (IDEs)

An Integrated Development Environment (IDE) is a software tool that helps programmers write code more efficiently.

# VSCode (Visual Studio Code)

1. Download VSCode from the browser using this link: [Download VSCode](https://code.visualstudio.com/download) and install it on your computer.
2. Configure environment variables.
3. It supports various programming languages.
4. Has built-in Git support.
